metadata.dc:author: Vilariño Mosquera, A
metadata.dc:description: Authors study digestive atresia mortality in relation to different parameters such as type of atresia, weight at birth and associated malformations. Mortality increases depending on whether the atresia be single or multiple, this increase being quite obvious when single or multiple atresia is associated with trisomy.
metadata.dc:title: Estudio de la mortalidad en la atresia digestiva Su relación con peso y malformación. Parte II.
[Study of digestive atresia mortality. Its relation with weight and malformation. Part II (author's transl)].
